alex.mojaki.boxes

Class AbstractPowerBox<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • alex.mojaki.boxes.AbstractPowerBox<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Box<T>, PowerBox<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractUpgradedBox, DefaultPowerBox

    public abstract class AbstractPowerBox<T>
extends Object
implements PowerBox<T>
    This class supplies the logic of applying middleware and observers stored in a family, without specifying how the value or family is stored.

      • rawGet

        protected abstract T rawGet()
        Return the raw value this box represents, which may then be processed by middleware and observers. This can mean returning a field, the result of a calculation as in a View, the value of an inner box as in an AbstractUpgradedBox, or anything else.

      • rawSet

        protected abstract void rawSet(T value)
        Store the value this box represents, after middleware has been applied but before notifying ChangeObservers. This can mean assigning a field, calling set on an inner box, etc.
